'''''Knights of the Old Republic'' 4''' is the fourth issue in the [[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic (comic series)|''Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic'']] series of comics.

==Opening crawl==
{{OpeningCrawl
|name=COMMENCEMENT<br />"PART 4 (OF SIX)"
|text=After discovering his fellow students dead at the feet of
their own Masters, Padawan ZAYNE CARRICK runs
for his life, aided only by GRYPH, a Snivvian con artist.
Blamed for the murders, the two flee into the Lower
City of Taris, staying just a step ahead of the Masters.

Gryph hopes a pair of Arkanian refugees will help them
find a way offworld. The addled inventor known only as
CAMPER and his protector, the fierce JARAEL, aren't
interested. When Zayne's Masters arrive, however, the
Arkanians suddenly launch into action&mdash;and into orbit!

But what had been camouflaged as the Arkanians'
home on Taris&mdash;the junk hauler LAST RESORT&mdash;hasn't
flown in years. And it certainly hasn't faced the Republic
patrols that await them, even now, in space&hellip;}}

==Plot summary==
With the Taris Orbital Patrols on their tail, the barely-spaceworthy [[The Last Resort (starship)|''Last Resort'']] makes its way into [[Taris/Legends|Taris]]' asteroid field. With power and transmissions restored thanks to [[Gorman Vandrayk|Camper]], Zayne Carrick makes a transmission to the [[Jedi Enclave]] on [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]], hoping to convince [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]], [[Vandar Tokare]], that he is innocent of [[Padawan Massacre|killing his fellow Padawans]]. Vandar finds this hard to believe, but he does believe that Zayne may have a diseased mind and therefore doesn't remember actually killing his friends. He suggests that Zayne return to Taris and seek help from one of the [[Jedi Consular]]s in restoring his sanity. With the transmission cut short by [[Jarael]] due to being brought out of the asteroid field, Zayne remembers something odd about the Jedi masters on Taris: all but one were Consulars.

Zayne decides that in order to find clues as to why the Jedi on Taris turned on their own Padawans, something must have happened on the [[Rogue Moon]] where he had had a training mission a couple of days earlier.

On the surface of the moon with Jarael, Zayne discovers the remains of the Jedi's bulk-lifter droid, [[T1-LB|Elbee]], and hopes that he may be able to recover the droids memory hologram too see if anything of importance regarding his masters actions is saved on it. At that moment, however, Zayne spots his master [[Lucien Draay|Lucien]] and the [[Taris Civil Authority|Taris authorities]] descending on them with weapons drawn.

